  • Short name: stroke
  • Variable label: Stroke
  • Variable description: Diagnosis of stroke or cerebral vascular disease since the last wave
  • Domain: Diseases
  • Value type: categorical
  • Category coding:

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute stroke from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedimX == 8 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute stroke_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if stroke == 1, stroke_age = heage
  • if stroke == 0, stroke_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, stroke_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == 8 | ELSA_w1$hedim02 == 8 | ELSA_w1$hedim03 == 
    8 | ELSA_w1$hedim04 == 8 | ELSA_w1$hedim05 == 8 | ELSA_w1$hedim06 == 8 | 
    ELSA_w1$hedim07 == 8)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$stroke == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w1$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$stroke == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w1$heage[which(ELSA_ds_w1$stroke == 
    1)], "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute stroke from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedimX == 8 into 1
  • hedia01 == -9 and hedimX == -1 into 997
  • hedia01 == -8 and hedimX == -1 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute stroke_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if stroke == 1, stroke_age = HeAgeRY - ybirth
  • if stroke == 0, stroke_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, stroke_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke[which(ELSA_w2$hedim01 == 8 | ELSA_w2$hedim02 == 8 | ELSA_w2$hedim03 == 
    8 | ELSA_w2$hedim04 == 8 | ELSA_w2$hedim05 == 8 | ELSA_w2$hedim06 == 8 | 
    ELSA_w2$hedim07 == 8 | ELSA_w2$hedim08 == 8)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke[which(ELSA_w2$hedia01 == -9 & ELSA_w2$hedim01 == -1)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke[which(ELSA_w2$hedia01 == -8 & ELSA_w2$hedim01 == -1)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$stroke == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgeRY %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9))] <- ELSA_w2$HeAgeRY[which(ELSA_ds_w2$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgeRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))] - ELSA_w2$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w2$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgeRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))]
ELSA_ds_w2$stroke_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w2$stroke_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute stroke from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • dhedimst == 1 into 1
  • dhedimst == 0 into 0
  • dhedimst == -1 into 996

To compute stroke_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if stroke == 1, stroke_age = heagery - ybirth
  • if stroke == 0, stroke_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, stroke_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w3$id)
ELSA_ds_w3$stroke <- car::recode(ELSA_w3$dhedimst, "-1=996")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3$stroke_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w3$id))
ELSA_ds_w3$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$stroke == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w3$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w3$heagery %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] <- ELSA_w3$heagery[which(ELSA_ds_w3$stroke == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heagery %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] - ELSA_w3$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w3$stroke == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heagery %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)]
ELSA_ds_w3$stroke_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w3$stroke_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.4.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute stroke from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • hedimst == 1 into 1
  • hedimst == -9 into 997
  • hedimst == -8 into 998
  • hedimst == 0 into 0

To compute stroke_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if stroke == 1, stroke_age = heagery-ybirth
  • if stroke == 0, stroke_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -2 into 991
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, stroke_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w4$id)
ELSA_ds_w4$stroke <- car::recode(ELSA_w4$hedimst, "-8=998;-9=997")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4$stroke_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$stroke == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$stroke_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagery %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9, -2))] <- ELSA_w4$heagery[which(ELSA_ds_w4$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagery %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))] - ELSA_w4$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w4$stroke == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagery %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))]
ELSA_ds_w4$stroke_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w4$stroke_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;-2=991;NA=999")
